        "variants": [
            {
                "name": "Link",
                "boxing_ring_title": "The Champion of Hyrule",
                "type": "Default"
            }
        ],
        "tips": [
            {
                "title": "Link's Origins",
                "content": "Link first appeared in The Legend of Zelda on the NES. Even back then, he had a wide inventory of items, including the Bow, Boomerang, and Bombs.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "In His Series",
                "content": "Link is the main protagonist of the series The Legend of Zelda. He has pointy ears and wields a sword and shield. In the Zelda games, Link uses items like bombs and arrows to defeat enemies and solve puzzles.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Who Is the Hero?",
                "content": "Despite being the hero, Link's name only appears in the title of five games. Can you name them? One might be trickier to remember than the others!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Clothing \"of the Wild\"",
                "content": "Link's second color variation is his Hero of the Wild armor, which dresses him in his traditional green garb. You can obtain this armor in Breath of the Wild by completing all of the shrines.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Bow and Arrows (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "The power and distance of the arrow increases as it's charged. Arrows can stick in the ground or walls, and if you pick one up and use this move again, you can fire off two arrows at once.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Boomerang (Side Special)",
                "content": "The Boomerang is the strongest the moment it's thrown. Flick the control stick quickly when you press the button to increase distance and power. If you don't catch the returning Boomerang, it will fly off.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Remote Bomb Recovery (Down Special)",
                "content": "If you are launched off the stage, you can use the Remote Bomb to blast yourself back toward the stage. It's very hard to pull off, but it might work as a last resort!",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Remote Bomb's Traits (Down Special)",
                "content": "You can detonate whenever you want, but keep in mind that Link will be damaged by the explosion too. The bomb will explode after a certain period or when hit with a fire attack.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Ancient Bow and Arrow (Final Smash)",
                "content": "Link shoots a powerful, blue glowing arrow that explodes on contact and launches opponents. The arrow will still explode if it hits a wall or the ground, and it can hit multiple opponents.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Sword Slice (Side Smash Attack)",
                "content": "If Link's damage is at 0% or he has full stamina in a stamina battle, he can shoot a sword beam by using his side smash attack.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Double Sword Slice (Side Smash Attack)",
                "content": "Press the button again to attack a second time. The second attack has more launching power.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Link's Air Attacks",
                "content": "Link's down and up air attacks, Downward Thrust and Jump Thrust, are from Zelda II - The Adventure of Link. In that game, they're learned from town swordsmen.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Jump Slash (Dash Attack)",
                "content": "Link's dash attack strikes with almost as much force as a smash attack. The point of his sword is especially painful.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Hylian Shield's Strength",
                "content": "Link's Hylian Shield is capable of stopping even the most powerful of projectiles. This means you won't take any damage at all.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Hylian Shield's Limits",
                "content": "Link's Hylian Shield can block projectiles, but it won't block anything while you're in the middle of attacking.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            }
        ],
        "fighters": [
