                "name": "Daisy",
                "boxing_ring_title": "Sarasaland's Chipper Princess",
                "type": "Default"
            }
        ],
        "tips": [
            {
                "title": "Daisy's Origins",
                "content": "Daisy debuted in Super Mario Land released in 1989. Mario saved her from a space alien named Tatanga, and the two escaped riding the Sky Pop.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "In Her Series",
                "content": "Sarasaland's Princess. She's more down-to-earth and energetic than Peach. She gives it her all at sporting events and parties, but tries to keep the mood friendly.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Toad (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "A Toad will risk its life to protect Daisy. If an attack hits the Toad, it will unleash a counter and launch opponents in front of Daisy.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Daisy Bomber (Side Special)",
                "content": "Attack an opponent with a powerful hip bash. You can use it as many times as you want in the air, so it's helpful for returning to the stage.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Daisy Parasol (Up Special)",
                "content": "Jump up, open the parasol, and slowly float down. It's great to use for returning to the stage, but the parasol can hit opponents too, so you can use it for attacks.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Vegetable (Down Special)",
                "content": "Of the eight types, the vegetable with the wrinkly face is the strongest. If you throw it while tapping the control stick in a direction, it can do over 30% damage!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Daisy Blossom (Final Smash)",
                "content": "Daisy's Final Smash puts opponents to sleep with a hypnotic dance. Pick up the daisies that appear to recover some health.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            }
        ],
        "fighters": [
            {
