        "variants": [
            {
                "name": "Diddy Kong",
                "boxing_ring_title": "The Acrobat",
                "type": "Default"
            }
        ],
        "tips": [
            {
                "title": "Diddy Kong's Origins",
                "content": "The small and agile Diddy Kong first appeared in the SNES title Donkey Kong Country in 1994, where he was a valuable partner to DK.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "In His Series",
                "content": "Diddy Kong appears as Donkey Kong's best friend and trusted partner in Donkey Kong Country. He lacks the power to defeat some enemies, but there's something to be said for his quick dash and high jumps.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Peanut Popgun (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "Overcharging the Peanut Popgun makes it backfire, but it'll do a ton of damage to foes that it hits!",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Peanut Popgun's Sign (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "While charging, watch for when Diddy grabs his hat! That's the sign that the Peanut Popgun's about to backfire.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Peanut Popgun Projectiles (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "The peanuts you fire can be caught by enemies if they time it right. Charge the move to make the peanuts harder to catch.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Monkey Flip (Side Special)",
                "content": "If you grab foes in the air, you'll release them more quickly than if you grab them on the ground. Be ready to use a speedy follow-up attack.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Monkey Flip to Flying Kick (Side Special)",
                "content": "While performing this move, you can press the attack button to launch a flying kick that deals considerable damage and has good launching power.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Uses for Monkey Flip (Side Special)",
                "content": "After grabbing on to opponents with this move, press the attack button to launch them sideways or press up to jump off their head!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Monkey Flip Technique (Side Special)",
                "content": "You can use this move again in the air after jumping off the first enemy you attack. Useful for when you're fighting a lot of enemies...",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Monkey Flip's Characteristics (Side Special)",
                "content": "If you use this move without triggering the flying kick part, you can use Rocketbarrel Boost! It's a great way to recover if you've been launched!",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Steering Rocketbarrel Boost (Up Special)",
                "content": "You can indicate a direction while this is charging to fly in that direction. You can even steer while flying!",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Rocketbarrel Boost (Up Special)",
                "content": "If someone attacks Diddy Kong when he's wearing his Rocketbarrel Pack, it'll break free and fly off on its own.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Warnings for Rocketbarrel Boost (Up Special)",
                "content": "You can also move horizontally. You'll go right through enemies even if they're shielding, but if you go over the edge, you're done for!",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Rocketbarrel Boost Techniques (Up Special)",
                "content": "If you fly up through a platform and land on it, the Rocketbarrel Pack will explode on contact with the platform, blasting nearby enemies.",
                "level": "Advanced"
            },
            {
                "title": "Rocketbarrel Boost Cut Loose (Up Special)",
                "content": "If Diddy Kong is hit while using this move, the Rocketbarrel will fly off on its own. You can control it slightly using the control stick.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Banana Peel (Down Special)",
                "content": "In this move, Diddy throws a banana peel behind him. Foes who step on it fall clumsily to the ground. Have a nice trip!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Banana Peel (Down Special)",
                "content": "You can't whip out another banana peel if one of yours is still in play, but each one will vanish after being thrown twice.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Items and Banana Peel (Down Special)",
                "content": "If you're holding an item when you throw the peel, you'll throw both at the same time. However, if it's a two-handed item, you won't throw it.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Hyper Rocketbarrel (Final Smash)",
                "content": "Diddy Kong flies around the screen in all directions using the latest Rocketbarrel technology. For the final hit, it'll target the opponent who was hit the most, but it'll catch nearby fighters as well.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Hand Clap (Down Tilt Attack)",
                "content": "It's a quick move that doesn't leave Diddy Kong vulnerable long, making it easy to use on the ground as a diversion. You also have a chance for a follow-up attack (such as an up smash) after it hits.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Screw Kick (Forward Air Attack)",
                "content": "With long reach and long hit time, this move is good at restricting an opponent's actions. It can be used as a diversion in the air, or even as an attack after dashing into a short hop.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            }
        ],
        "fighters": [
