        "variants": [
            {
                "name": "Male",
                "boxing_ring_title": "The Tactician Magician",
                "type": "Same character"
            },
            {
                "name": "Female",
                "boxing_ring_title": "The Tactician Magician",
                "type": "Same character"
            }
        ],
        "tips": [
            {
                "title": "Robin's Origins",
                "content": "Robin debuted in Fire Emblem Awakening, a 2013 release in North America. As the customizable avatar of the player, he or she fought alongside Chrom.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "In Their Series",
                "content": "The avatar from Fire Emblem Awakening. You can set the avatar's personality and appearance. In Awakening, Robin is saved by Chrom and joins his militia as a tactician.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Nosferatu",
                "content": "In Fire Emblem Awakening, Robin wasn't able to use Nosferatu in his or her base class of Tactician—only by reclassing into a Dark Mage.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Thunder (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "If you launch this move without charging it up, Robin will cast Thunder. It's not very powerful, but its fast speed can take foes by surprise.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Thunder Types (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "Robin will use one of four magic spells, depending on how long you charge Thunder. The color the tome glows indicates which spell will be used.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Thunder Charge Level 1 (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "Once the tome starts glowing yellow, you can cast Elthunder. It's more powerful than Thunder and travels farther, but it's not quite as fast.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Thunder Charge Level 2 (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "A reddish purple glow means that Thunder has charged into Arcthunder! A current with high attack power appears when this move connects.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Thunder at Max Charge (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "When Thunder is fully charged, it becomes Thoron! The high-speed beam can deal damage to multiple opponents at once.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Reaching Thunder's Limits (Neutral Special)",
                "content": "Thunder can be used up to 20 times in a row, but stronger tomes use it up faster. Elthunder counts as 3 uses, Arcthunder as 5, and Thoron as 8.",
                "level": "Advanced"
            },
            {
                "title": "Reaching Arcfire's Limits (Side Special)",
                "content": "Arcfire can be used up to six times in a row. Once it's used up, it'll be about 12 seconds before you can use the move again.",
                "level": "Advanced"
            },
            {
                "title": "Elwind (Up Special)",
                "content": "The first Elwind has a meteor effect right after it comes out. When the Elwinds hit the ground, they create a gust of wind that pushes opponents back.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Reaching Elwind's Limits (Up Special)",
                "content": "Elwind causes two blasts to propel you upward, and it also uses your tome twice. If you've only got one tome use left, you won't be able to double Elwind!",
                "level": "Advanced"
            },
            {
                "title": "Reaching Nosferatu's Limits (Down Special)",
                "content": "Nosferatu is a useful technique that can recover health, but it can only be used three times in a row and takes up to 30 seconds to recharge.",
                "level": "Advanced"
            },
            {
                "title": "Pair Up (Final Smash)",
                "content": "If Chrom's attack connects and you perform this successfully, all of Robin's tomes and the Levin Sword will be fully recovered afterward.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Neutral Attack",
                "content": "If the third hit is fire, it will launch opponents with great force. The wind flurry attack repeatedly slashes opponents and deals a lot of damage. Both will use up a tome charge.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Undercut (Down Air Attack)",
                "content": "This attack doesn't have a meteor effect with the Bronze Sword, but it does with the Levin Sword.",
                "level": "Advanced"
            },
            {
                "title": "Neutral Air Attack with the Levin Sword",
                "content": "Press the special move and attack buttons at the same time in the air to switch to a Levin Sword even when holding a Bronze Sword. You can perform a neutral air attack by doing this.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Reaching the Levin Sword's Limits",
                "content": "After eight uses of the Levin Sword, you'll throw it away and be unable to use it for 10 seconds. Use a neutral attack while grounded to draw a Bronze Sword.",
                "level": "Advanced"
            },
            {
                "title": "Levin Sword's Recovery Time",
                "content": "When you've used up the Levin Sword, perform smash attacks with the Bronze Sword or directional midair attacks to reduce the wait.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Using the Levin Sword",
                "content": "You cannot use the Levin Sword at the start of the battle, but once time passes, it will be available to use. On the other hand, tomes can be used from the start.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Throwing Tome and Levin Sword",
                "content": "When Robin discards tomes and Levin Swords after using them up, they can hurt opponents they hit. They can even be grabbed and thrown!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Tome and Levin Sword Recovery",
                "content": "As a general rule, the remaining uses of tomes and Levin Swords won't reset until they're all used up or Robin gets KO'd.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Tome Care",
                "content": "The third strike of Robin's neutral attack combo uses the same tome as Arcfire. When you run out of one attack, you also run out of the other.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Tome Changes",
                "content": "It's difficult to notice in the middle of a battle, but the cover of the tome Robin uses actually changes depending on the spell being used.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Flurry Attack and Elwind",
                "content": "Robin's flurry attack uses the same tome as Elwind. If you use it up with the flurry attack, you won't be able to use Elwind for recovery!",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            },
            {
                "title": "Regenerating Tomes and Swords",
                "content": "If you've used up a tome or your Levin Sword, try KO'ing some opponents. That'll shorten the time you have to wait to use them again.",
                "level": "Intermediate"
            }
        ],
        "fighters": [
