        "variants": [
            {
                "name": "Min Min",
                "boxing_ring_title": "The Ramen Bomber",
                "type": "Default"
            }
        ],
        "tips": [
            {
                "title": "Min Min's Origins",
                "content": "Min Min first appeared in the game ARMS in 2017. She's a well-known worker at the Mintendo Noodle House, which serves delicious ramen. She actually entered the Grand Prix to advertise her shop!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "In Her Series",
                "content": "Min Min is petite with skinny arms, but when she charges up, her left ARM turns into a dragon, empowering her punches. She also likes to employ kicks in the air, deflecting an opponent's ARM.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Punch",
                "content": "Use the attack button to unleash a punch with the left ARM, and use the special-move button to punch with the right ARM. Flick the stick with either move to turn it into a smash attack, increasing range and power.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Punching Power",
                "content": "The punch unleashed by flicking the stick is at its strongest just before the ARM is fully extended. The attack is weaker at the beginning of the punch and when the ARM reaches its maximum range.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "The ARM's Charged Smash",
                "content": "Holding down the attack or special-move button and flicking the stick will charge up power for a charged smash attack. This will also change the move that is used.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Shifting ARM Arc",
                "content": "If you're on the ground and you tilt up or down just before unleashing a punch to the left or right, you can move the ARMS in an arc. The way the ARM bends depends on the type of ARM.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Punching and...",
                "content": "Even with an ARM extended, you can still move around and jump. During smash attacks, you can attack with the other ARM, too!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Attack Forward and Backward",
                "content": "It's possible for Min Min to attack in both directions! While attacking in one direction with one ARM extended, move the stick in the opposite direction and press the button for the other ARM to send it that way!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "When the ARM Bounces Back",
                "content": "Your ARMS will bounce back if they hit a wall or the floor. They'll also bounce back if an opponent shields the attack, which will leave you vulnerable to a counterattack!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Changing into a Dragon",
                "content": "The left ARM will gain power and change into a dragon when you throw an opponent or when your Final Smash is ready. Shortly after throwing an opponent, or if Min Min cannot move, the ARM will return to normal.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Three ARMS in One",
                "content": "The right ARM has three variations: Ramram is very bendy, making it easier to hit opponents. Megawatt is slow but powerful. The Dragon can extend out and shoot lasers!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Ramram",
                "content": "The Ramram is a light ARM that will arc in flight. It's not powerful, but it extends quickly and is bendy, keeping enemies on their toes. It can extend through walls or the ground while you are airborne.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Megawatt",
                "content": "The Megawatt is a heavy ARM that is a lot like an iron ball. When charged, it becomes engulfed in electricity. It doesn't arc easily or extend quickly, but it's super powerful. Perfect for a final blow.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Dragon",
                "content": "The Dragon is an ARM that is shaped like a dragon. It can be equipped on both arms. If you press the attack button when the ARM is fully extended in a smash attack, it fires a laser!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "ARMS Jump (Up Special)",
                "content": "When neither ARM is extended and you're on the ground, this move will send you flying upward. You'll be invincible the moment you jump, and charging the move will extend the height and invincibility time!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Maneuvering the ARMS Jump (Up Special)",
                "content": "If you tilt the stick to the left or right before you jump, you can leap diagonally. You can also move to the left or right while falling.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Using ARM Hook (Up Special)",
                "content": "Use this move in the air to extend an ARM diagonally upward. If it hits an edge, you'll be able to dangle from the edge instead of falling. Tilt up on the stick or press a button to pull yourself up.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "ARM Change (Down Special)",
                "content": "The right ARM can be swapped between Ramram, Megawatt, and Dragon. You won't be able to swap ARMS out while attacking or if you are currently unable to move.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "ARMS Rush (Final Smash)",
                "content": "The left ARM will transform into a dragon to unleash an attack. Only one opponent will get caught up in the rush of punches that various ARMS fighters will swoop in to deliver, sending that fighter flying.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Kung Fu Combo and Flurry Attack",
                "content": "Hit the attack or special-move button quickly on the ground to unleash a three-kick attack. Hit the button multiple times during the combo to turn it into a flurry attack!",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Reflecting Projectiles (Up Smash Attack)",
                "content": "Min Min's up smash is a kick capable of reflecting projectile attacks. Reflected projectiles will increase in speed and power, however.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            },
            {
                "title": "Neutral Air Attack",
                "content": "Min Min's neutral air attack swings an ARM out at opponents. The speed and power of the attack will change depending on which ARM is currently equipped.",
                "level": "Beginner"
            }
        ],
        "fighters": [
            {
                "id": "76",
                "name": "Min Min",
                "slug": "min-min",
                "also_appears_in": []
            }
        ]
    },
